le plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"In Blue\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/moominvalley-official-soundtrack/1453752386|title=MOOMINVALLEY (Official Soundtrack) by Various Artists|date=19 April 2019|accessdate=26 February 2019}}</ref>\n| 2019\n| ''[[Moominvalley (TV series)#Music|MOOMINVALLEY (Official Soundtrack)]]''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Notes===\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Declan McKenna}}\n*[https://www.declanmckenna.net Official website]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McKenna, Declan}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Cheshunt]]\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century English singers]]\n[[Category:English child singers]]\n[[Category:English male singers]]\n[[Category:English rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:English rock pianists]]\n[[Category:English rock singers]]\n[[Category:English singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records artists]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Hertfordshire]]\n[[Category:21st-century pianists]]\n[[Category:Male guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century guitarists]]\n[[Category:Male pianists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "name_user": "Wezle", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eZeros (2019\u2013present):Cleaned up grammar, changed structure of the sentence to remove excessive use of commas, and added a hyperlink.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Declan_McKenna"}
{"title_page": "Something New (Wiz Khalifa song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Something New\n| cover      = WizKhalifaSomethingNew.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Wiz Khalifa]] featuring [[Ty Dolla Sign]]\n| album      = [[Rolling Papers 2]]\n| released   = August 11, 2017\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2017\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=20}}\n| label      = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Wiz Khalifa|Cameron Thomaz]]|[[Ty Dolla Sign|Tyrone Griffin, Jr.]]|Dimitri McDowell}}\n| producer   = Ayo n Keyz & [[Hitmaka]]\n| chronology = [[Wiz Khalifa]]\n| prev_title = [[Gang Up]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = Type of Shit\n| next_year  = 2017\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Ty Dolla Sign]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Love U Better]]\n | prev_year  = 2017\n | title      = Something New\n | year       = 2017\n | next_title = [[Ego (Ella Eyre song)|Ego]]\n | next_year  = 2017\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Something New'''\"  is a song by American rapper [[Wiz Khalifa]] featuring [[Taylor Gang Records|Taylor Gang]] label mate [[Ty Dolla Sign]] for his sixth studio album ''[[Rolling Papers 2]]'' (2018). It was released for [[Music download|digital download]] on August 11, 2017 by [[Atlantic Records]] as the album's [[lead single]]. The song was re-released on March 16, 2020 as the official lead single off Wiz Khalifa's upcoming 7th studio album. It was produced by Ayo n Keyz & [[Hitmaka]]. It heavily samples [[Zapp (band)|Zapp]]'s 1986 single \"[[Computer Love (Zapp song)|Computer Love]]\". The song received renewed popularity in 2020, thanks to its use in [[TikTok]] videos.\n\n==Background==\nWiz and Ty previewed the song and clips of the music video several times on [[Instagram]] throughout July 2017.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c4W7M6w3S88</ref><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=550j5yxgOzo</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Something New\" is a \"feel-good love song\" featuring smooth, sultry vocals and a [[Rhythm#Composite rhythm|rhythmic]] chorus\u00a0from Ty Dolla $ign.<ref name=\"ComplexTikTok\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/tiktok-songs-worth-listening-to/rod-wave-hear-on-ice|title=12 Songs Blowing Up on TikTok (That Are Actually Worth Listening to)|last=McKinney|first=Jessica|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"Something New\" was the most added song to mainstream [[urban contemporary]] radio upon its release.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.facebook.com/wizkhalifa/photos/a.133118481141.141020.12138756141/10155468647631142/?type=3&theater|title=Words can't explain how excited I am. Thank you for the support. Thank you @tydollasign @hitmaka @soundz and everyone else involved.|publisher=Facebook|accessdate=August 23, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==TikTok dance challenge==\n\nIn early 2020, the song began going viral on video-sharing app [[TikTok]], due to a dance challenge. The challenge sees participants line up behind each other, with one person in front to kick off the dance, and everyone else then proceeding to push each elbow out to the side before [[shimmy|shimmying]] along to the song's chorus and then clapping along to the beat.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/ciara-and-russell-wilsons-family-take-on-viral-tiktok-challenge-news.106789.html?_amp|title=Ciara & Russell Wilson's Family Take On Viral TikTok Challenge|last=S.|first=Lynn|website=HotNewHipHop|date=March 19, 2020|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2020/03/19/jennifer-lopez-alex-rodriguez-family-tiktok-dance-challenge-something-new/|title=A-Rod & J.Lo Team Up With Their Kids For Epic TikTok Video & Fans Call It 'The Best' \u2014 Watch|website=[[HollywoodLife]]|last=Boren|first=Jade|date=March 19, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nOn August 14, 2017, Wiz uploaded the official music video for \"Something New\".<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qxGapEwtq6g</ref> The plot involves various women robbing Wiz at his own house party behind his back. The video ends with all the women sneaking out and driving away while thanking him on [[Snapchat]] for allowing them to trick him. As of February 2020, the video has over 97 million views. Cameos include [[G-Eazy]], [[Lil Dicky]], [[Demi Lovato]], [[Jamie Foxx]], [[Juicy J]], [[Jason Derulo]], [[O.T. Genasis]], [[Todd Gurley]] and Bob Ross.\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada|94|artist=Wiz Khalifa|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Hungarysingle|34|year=2017|week=33|artist=Wiz Khalifa|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 25, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|92|artist=Wiz Khalifa|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 23, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardrandbhiphop|37|artist=Wiz Khalifa|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 23, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardrhythmic|24|artist=Wiz Khalifa|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 17, 2017}}\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Country\n!Date\n!Format\n!Label\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| United States\n|August 11, 2017\n| [[Music download|Digital download]]<ref name=\"iTunes\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/something-new-feat-ty-dolla-%24ign-single/id1267573353|title=Something New by Wiz Khalifa featuring Ty Dolla Sign |work=[[iTunes Store]] (US) |accessdate=August 23, 2017}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\" | {{flatlist|\n* [[Taylor Gang Records|Taylor Gang]]\n* [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n}}\n|-\n| August&nbsp;22,&nbsp;2017\n| [[Urban contemporary|Urban]] radio<ref name=\"allaccess\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823091244/https://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases|archive-date=August 23, 2017|title=Urban/UAC Future Releases|publisher=All Access|accessdate=August 23, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Wiz Khalifa singles}}\n{{Ty Dolla Sign}}\n\n[[Category:2017 songs]]\n[[Category:Wiz Khalifa songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Wiz Khalifa]]\n[[Category:2017 singles]]\n[[Category:Ty Dolla Sign songs]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ty Dolla Sign]]\n[[Category:TikTok songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Something New\n| cover      = WizKhalifaSomethingNew.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Wiz Khalifa]] featuring [[Ty Dolla Sign]]\n| album      = [[Rolling Papers 2]]\n| released   = August 11, 2017\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2017\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=20}}\n| label      = [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Wiz Khalifa|Cameron Thomaz]]|[[Ty Dolla Sign|Tyrone Griffin, Jr.]]|Dimitri McDowell}}\n| producer   = Ayo n Keyz & [[Hitmaka]]\n| chronology = [[Wiz Khalifa]]\n| prev_title = [[Gang Up]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = Type of Shit\n| next_year  = 2017\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Ty Dolla Sign]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Love U Better]]\n | prev_year  = 2017\n | title      = Something New\n | year       = 2017\n | next_title = [[Ego (Ella Eyre song)|Ego]]\n | next_year  = 2017\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Something New'''\"  is a song by American rapper [[Wiz Khalifa]] featuring [[Taylor Gang Records|Taylor Gang]] label mate [[Ty Dolla Sign]] for his sixth studio album ''[[Rolling Papers 2]]'' (2018). It was released for [[Music download|digital download]] on August 11, 2017 by [[Atlantic Records]] as the al